owl:Ontology.dc:abstract: The Intent Based Control Loop Ontology (IBCLO) provides a set of classes, properties, and restrictions that can be used to represent and interchange provenance and metadata information relating to Prometheus metric information.
owl:Ontology.dc:creator: Alex Randles
owl:Ontology.dc:description: The Intent Based Control Loop Ontology (IBCLO) is used to capture information which relates to metric information within the Prometheus monitoring system.
owl:Ontology.dc:title: Intent Based Control Loop Ontology (IBCLO)
